PN,31218
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1784575122
OL,3,CWelfare, tax and migration: The
OL,4,Cchallenges facing Andy Burnham
OL,6,FThe question will now be which world
OL,7,Fleader is Burnham likely to call
OL,8,Ffirst, a custom of new leaders getting
OL,9,Fin touch with allies at the start of
OL,10,Ftheir premiership.
OL,12,FA new Cabinet
OL,14,FThe rumour mill in Westminster has
OL,15,Fbeen working overtime since Burnham
OL,16,Freturned as an MP over who he will
OL,17,Fselect for his Cabinet.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31219
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1784575122
OL,3,CWelfare, tax and migration: The
OL,4,Cchallenges facing Andy Burnham
OL,6,FIn his speech on Friday, Burnham said:
OL,7,F" I haven't made any decisions yet
OL,8,Fabout who will be in that top team.
OL,9,FBut I will soon. And when I have, you
OL,10,Fwill see it reflects all parts of our
OL,11,Fparty".
OL,13,FThe leading question is who will
OL,14,Freplace Rachel Reeves as Chancellor.
OL,15,FThe current favourite for the job is
OL,16,FHome Secretary Shabana Mahmood.
OL,18,FMahmood is in the blue Labour faction,
OL,19,Fleaning more to the right of the party.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31220
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1784575122
OL,3,CWelfare, tax and migration: The
OL,4,Cchallenges facing Andy Burnham
OL,6,FEd Miliband was also slated as a
OL,7,Fpotential candidate for the job, but
OL,8,Fis reportedly considered too disliked
OL,9,Fby too many powerful interests, from
OL,10,Ftrade union leaders to business
OL,11,Fleaders, to investors and the right-
OL,12,Fwing media. The i Paper reported he is
OL,13,Flikely to be made foreign secretary.
OL,15,FThere are several former members of
OL,16,Fthe Cabinet expected to return,
OL,17,Fincluding John Healey, who is also
OL,18,Ftipped for foreign secretary, with Wes
OL,19,FStreeting, Angela Rayner and Lucy
OL,20,FPowell all expected to be part of
OL,21,FBurnham's top team.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G20/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31221
SC,0021
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1784575122
OL,3,CWelfare, tax and migration: The
OL,4,Cchallenges facing Andy Burnham
OL,6,FSeveral key members of Burnham's
OL,7,Fcampaign team are expected to join the
OL,8,FCabinet, with a return for Transport
OL,9,FSecretary Louise Haigh and first-time
OL,10,Fjobs for Anneliese Midgley and Sally
OL,11,FJamieson.
OL,13,FBurnham will also need to tackle
OL,14,Fissues on the environment, tackling
OL,15,Fthe housing crisis, social care
OL,16,Freforms, net zero targets, reducing
OL,17,Fjury trials, and transport systems
OL,18,Facross the country.
OL,20,FIt is unlikely to be a peaceful summer
OL,21,Ffor the MP for Makerfield.
